comments.text:
I think the morale of the story is...our real lives aren't as fantastical 
as it seems online so lets stop expecting life to be like what it says 
online.. i guess the healthiest is living in the world of ''what is'', not 
in a world of '' wouldn't it be nice if'' world. 

Indeed everyone else's lives always seem way more interesting than your 
own, but lets all  remember we don't see that pain and hustle of going 
through real life hustles like paying the bills, getting tasks 
done...etc... online. We only see the highlights of other people's lives 
and i can guarantee a highlight is only filled with the happy stuff or 
''the cool stuff''. Don't compare your life to someone else's highlights of 
their life~ your life is just as cool as theirs too! You just don't see it 
because its your own life.﻿
